<div id="c6">
<p>What you&#8217;re encountering is that while you might be good at programming, so are a lot of other people; you&#8217;re also good at other things (of which writing I think is a symptom and not a cause), and there are comparatively fewer people who are also good at those &#8216;other things.&#8217;</p>

<p>I say writing is a symptom not a cause because I think writing is simply the channel you&#8217;ve been using to express great ideas that you want to put into more concrete action.  This is all theorycraft, however ;)</p>

<p>In any case, I&#8217;ve always been of the opinion that one should do what one loves in life, and thus I&#8217;d heartily encourage you to pursue those &#8216;other things&#8217; with all your heart, soul and body.</p>

