<div id="c25">
<p>I&#8217;ve been debating the link between passion and greatness myself.  Unlike you, I have never been a great programmer - I&#8217;d gotten by for several years as one solely on my aptitude for making computers do what I want.  I never coded in my free time, I never liked coding, but it was easy work (for me) that paid well, so I did it.  But I eventually realized I would never be great at it unless I deeply cared about it.  And I didn&#8217;t.</p>

<p>Don&#8217;t let aptitude define you.  Find what you love and follow it.  If I step back and pay attention to the things I&#8217;m actually excited about, that get me animated and talking fast and waving my arms, it&#8217;s pretty clear what I should be doing.  In my case, it&#8217;s management, or at least the process of creating a viable corporate community, so I&#8217;m in the process of launching my third career.  We&#8217;ll see if I continue to care about it as I get more into it.</p>

<p>Good luck!</p>

